irs990.activityormissiondesc: THE FEDERAL CITY COUNCIL SERVES AS A CATALYST FOR PROGRESS IN THE DISTRICT OF COLUMBIA.
irs990.missiondesc: THE FEDERAL CITY COUNCIL WAS ESTABLISHED IN 1954 FOR THE PURPOSE OF ENHANCING WASHINGTON, DC BY SERVING AS A CATALYST FOR PROGRESS. THE COUNCIL UTILIZES THE TALENTS OF THE DISTRICT'S BUSINESS AND PROFESSIONAL LEADERS TO ADDRESS SOME OF THE MOST IMPORTANT AND CHALLENGING ISSUES FACING THE WASHINGTON, DC AREA.
irs990.desc: FISCAL STABILITY AND ECONOMIC DEVELOPMENT:THE FEDERAL CITY COUNCIL ENCOURAGES EFFORTS TO ENSURE THE LONG-TERM COMPETITIVENESS AND RESILIENCY OF THE DISTRICT'S ECONOMY. THESE EFFORTS INCLUDE PROMOTING A FAIR AND EQUITABLE TAX SYSTEM, PROMOTING EFFORTS TO SUPPORT DC BUSINESSES, AND ESTABLISHING THE DC POLICY WHICH PROVIDES UNBAISED ECONOMIC AND PUBLIC POLICY ANALYSES TO ELECTED OFFICIALS AND THE PUBLIC.

progsrvcaccomacty2grp.desc: TRANSPORTATION AND INFRASTRUCTURE:THE FEDERAL CITY COUNCIL UNDERTAKES ACTIVITIES TO ENCOURAGE REGIONAL TRANSPORTATION PLANNING AND COOPERATION, EXPLORE INNOVATIVE METHODS FOR FINANCING CRITICAL INFRASTRUCTURE IMPROVEMENTS, AND PROMOTE EFFORTS TO IMPROVE THE SAFETY AND RELIABILITY OF WMATA, THE REGION'S MASS TRANSIT SYSTEM.

progsrvcaccomacty3grp.desc: GENERAL MEMBERSHIP ACTIVITIES:THE FEDERAL CITY COUNCIL WAS ESTABLISHED IN 1954 TO FOCUS THE CREATIVITY, TALENT AND RESOURCES OF THE DISTRICT OF COLUMBIA'S TOP BUSINESS, EDUCATION AND PHILANTHROPIC LEADERS ON MAJOR CHALLENGES AND OPPORTUNITIES FACING THE CITY. THE COUNCIL IS A NON-PARTISAN ORGANIZATION WHOSE 220 MEMBERS WORK WITH THE DISTRICT AND FEDERAL GOVERNMENTS TO DEVISE AND IMPLEMENT SOLUTIONS TO IMPORTANT COMMUNITY PROBLEMS.

progsrvcaccomactyothergrp.desc: EDUCATION:THE FEDERAL CITY COUNCIL SERVES AS A TRUSTED PARTNER FOR EDUCATIONAL IMPROVEMENT IN THE DISTRICT OF COLUMBIA. WORKING CLOSELY WITH LOCAL AND FEDERAL STAKEHOLDERS, THE COUNCIL PROMOTES EFFORTS TO CREATE AN EDUCATIONAL SYSTEM IN WHICH ALL STUDENTS CAN GRADUATE FROM HIGH SCHOOL AND BE PREPARED FOR COLLEGE, CAREER AND LIFE.

form990partviisectionagrp.titletxt: CHIEF EXECUTIVE OFFICER AND EXECUTIVE DIRECTOR

supplementalinformationdetail.explanationtxt: THE COUNCIL IS EXEMPT FROM INCOME TAXES UNDER SECTION 501(C)(3) OF THE INTERNAL REVENUE CODE (IRC) AND IS CLASSIFIED AS OTHER THAN A PRIVATE FOUNDATION WITHIN THE MEANING OF SECTION 509(A)(1) OF THE IRC. ACCORDINGLY, NO PROVISION FOR INCOME TAXES HAS BEEN MADE IN THE ACCOMPANYING FINANCIAL STATEMENTS. MANAGEMENT BELIEVES THAT IT HAS NO MATERIAL UNCERTAIN TAX POSITIONS THAT WOULD REQUIRE RECOGNITION UNDER THE ACCOUNTING CODIFICATION GUIDANCE.

SOCIAL AND HEALTH CLUB COST REIMBURSEMENTS ARE PERMITTED FOR THE CEO, PURSUANT TO THE EMPLOYMENT CONTRACT APPROVED BY THE EXECUTIVE COMMITTEE. ANTHONY A. WILLIAMS, HEALTH OR SOCIAL CLUB DUES OR INIATION FEES $2,784, NOT INCLUDED IN TAXABLE COMPENSATION.

dispositionofassetsdetail.assetsdistriorexpnsspaiddesc: CASH BALANCE OF TEMPORARILY RESTRICTED CONTRIBUTIONS

supplementalinformationdetail.explanationtxt: EXPLANATION OF INVOLVEMENT: ANTHONY WILLIAMS, EXECUTIVE DIRECTOR AND CEO OF THE FEDERAL CITY COUNCIL, WAS NAMED BOARD CHAIR OF THE ANACOSTIA WATERFRONT TRUST, AN ORGANIZATION ESTABLISHED BY THE FEDERAL CITY COUNCIL TO FOCUS ON THE RESTORATION OF THE ANACOSTIA RIVER.
THE FEDERAL CITY COUNCIL ESTABLISHED THE DC POLICY CENTER TO PROVIDE UNBIASED ECONOMIC AND PUBLIC POLICY ANALYSES TO THE PUBLIC AND DECISION MAKERS.
THE FEDERAL CITY COUNCIL SPUN-OFF ITS ANACOSTIA RIVER INITIATIVE INTO A SEPARATE ORGANIZATION CALLED THE ANACOSTIA WATERFRONT TRUST.

supplementalinformationdetail.formandlinereferencedesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION A, LINE 1
supplementalinformationdetail.explanationtxt: LINE 1A: THE FEDERAL CITY COUNCIL'S EXECUTIVE COMMITTEE IS COMPRISED OF ITS OFFICERS, COMMITTEE CHAIRS AND 28 MEMBERS-AT-LARGE WHO ARE ELECTED BY THE MEMBERS. THE EXECUTIVE COMMITTEE SERVES AS THE COUNCIL'S BOARD OF DIRECTORS AND IS RESPONSIBLE FOR MANAGING THE ORGANIZATION'S PROPERTY, BUSINESS AND AFFAIRS.

supplementalinformationdetail.formandlinereferencedesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION A, LINE 2
supplementalinformationdetail.explanationtxt: CONRAD CAFRITZ AND CALVIN CAFRITZ ARE BROTHERS.

supplementalinformationdetail.formandlinereferencedesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION A, LINE 6
supplementalinformationdetail.explanationtxt: MEMBERS ARE CLASSIFIED BY SEVERAL FACTORS INCLUDING ANNUAL DUES, THE SIZE AND NATURE OF THE ORGANIZATIONS THEY REPRESENT AND THEIR ROLE ON THE COUNCIL, SUCH AS SERVING AS AN OFFICER OR COMMITTEE MEMBER.

supplementalinformationdetail.formandlinereferencedesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION A, LINE 7A
supplementalinformationdetail.explanationtxt: VOTING MEMBERS IN GOOD STANDING ELECT MEMBERS TO THE OFFICERS GROUP AND EXECUTIVE COMMITTEE.

supplementalinformationdetail.formandlinereferencedesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION A, LINE 7B
supplementalinformationdetail.explanationtxt: DECISIONS RATIFIED ANNUALLY BY THE FULL MEMEBRSHIP INCLUDE ADOPTION OF AN ANNUAL BUDGET, CHANGES TO BYLAWS AND ELECTION OF OFFICERS.

supplementalinformationdetail.formandlinereferencedesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 11B
supplementalinformationdetail.explanationtxt: THE FORM 990 IS INITIALLY REVIEWED BY THE DIRECTOR OF FINANCE AND CHIEF OPERAITNG OFFICER. IT IS THEN PROVIDED TO THE TREASURER, CHAIRMAN AND CEO FOR FINAL REVIEW AND APPROVAL. A COPY IS PROVIDED TO THE ENTIRE OFFICERS GROUP ONCE IT HAS BEEN SUBMITTED AND IS MADE AVAILALBE TO ALL TRUSTEES UPON REQUEST.

supplementalinformationdetail.formandlinereferencedesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 12C
supplementalinformationdetail.explanationtxt: THE ORGANIZATION'S STAFF AND BOARD REVIEW ALL TRANSACTIONS BEFORE THEY ARE EXECUTED TO IDENTIFY POTENTIAL CONFLITS OF INTEREST. IF A REAL OR PERCEVED CONFLICT OF INTEREST IS IDENTIFIED, THE TRANSACTION IS MODIFIED TO REMOVE THE CONFLICT OR THE TRANSACTION IS NOT EXECUTED. ADDITIONALY, AS PART OF THE ANNUAL INDEPENDENT AUDIT PROCESS, THE ORGANIZATION REVIEWS ALL TRANSACTIONS AT THE END OF EACH FISCAL YEAR TO IDENTIFY ANY CONFLICTS OF INTEREST OT RELATED PARTY TRANSACTIONS THAT MAY NOT HAVE BEEN PREVIOUSLY NOTED.

supplementalinformationdetail.formandlinereferencedesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 15
supplementalinformationdetail.explanationtxt: THE OFFICER'S GROUP DETERMINES THE COMPENSATION FOR THE CEO AND OTHER SENIOR EXECUTIVES ANUALLY. AMONG OTHER RESOURCES, THE OFFICER'S GROUP USES INDEPENDENTLY COLLECTED SALARY SURVEY DATA TO ENSURE STAFF SALARIES ARE COMMENSURATE WITH THOSE OF SIMILAR ORGANIZATIONS IN THE SAME MARKET. THE PROCESS LAST TOOK PLACE IN 2016. THE SAME PROCESS IS USED FOR DETERMING COMPENSATION FOR OTHER OFFICERS AND KEY EMPLOYEES. THE PROCESS LAST TOOK PLACE IN 2016.

supplementalinformationdetail.formandlinereferencedesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION C, LINE 19
supplementalinformationdetail.explanationtxt: THE ORGANIZATION PROVIDES GOVERNING DOCUMENTS, CONFLICT OF INTEREST POLICY AND FINANCIAL STATEMENTS UPON REQUEST.
